Data.event_text: 1 January  An increase in the value-added tax (VAT) rate to 12% is put into effect on luxury goods and services or those that fall into the luxury tax category.

links.text: -"Mengapa pemerintah berubah sikap soal PPN 12%?" [Why did the government changed its stance on 12% VAT?]. BBC News Indonesia. 1 January 2025. Retrieved 1 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: Indonesia is fully admitted as a member state of the BRICS group.

links.text: -Sá Pessoa, Gabriela (7 January 2025). "Indonesia is admitted to the BRICS bloc of developing nations". AP News. Retrieved 9 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: The Free Nutritious Meal (MBG) program of the Prabowo administration is officially started.

links.text: -"Makan Bergizi Gratis Dimulai 6 Januari di 26 Provinsi, Disiapkan dari 190 Dapur". VOI (in Indonesian). 5 January 2025. Retrieved 10 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: Shin Tae-yong is dismissed as coach of the Indonesia national football team amid multiple issues involving the team.

links.text: -"Indonesia sack coach Shin, citing World Cup target". Reuters. 6 January 2025. Retrieved 10 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: 8 January  At least four people die and eleven others are injured after a bus carrying a group of students from Bali crashes into several vehicles in Batu, East Java.

links.text: -"Bus Kecelakaan di Batu Angkut Rombongan Siswa SMK TI Global Bali". CNN Indonesia (in Indonesian). 9 January 2025. Retrieved 9 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: A fire engulfs the Glodok Plaza shopping center in Glodok, West Jakarta, killing eight people and leaving several missing.

links.text: -Ramadhanty, Dinda; Huda, Larissa (18 January 2025). "Bertambah 1 Kantong Jenazah, Korban Kebakaran Glodok Plaza Jadi 8 Orang". Kompas (in Indonesian). Retrieved 18 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: The government raises its highest volcanic eruption level over Mount Ibu in Halmahera following a major eruption.

links.text: -"Indonesia raises volcano alert to highest level after Mt. Ibu erupts". Xinhua. Retrieved 21 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: 20 January  Landslides caused by heavy rains in Denpasar and Klungkung, Bali kill at least nine people.

links.text: -"Longsor di Denpasar dan Klungkung Bali, 9 Orang Tewas". Detik (in Indonesian). Retrieved 21 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: Flooding and landslides in Pekalongan, Central Java kill at least 25 people.

links.text: -"Indonesia landslide death toll rises to 25". France 24. Retrieved 22 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: A fire hits a residential area on Jalan Kemayoran Gempol, Kemayoran, Central Jakarta, destroying more than 500 houses and displacing 1,797 residents.

links.text: -"Kronologi Kebakaran Kemayoran Api Muncul Di Satu Rumah Hingga Hanguskan Lebih Dari 500 Bangunan". Liputan 6 (in Indonesian). 21 January 2025. Retrieved 22 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: Indonesia and France sign an agreement to repatriate French national Serge Atlaoui, who has been in death row since 2007 in an Indonesian prison following a conviction for drug smuggling.

links.text: -"Indonesia agrees to repatriate ailing French national who has spent almost 20 years on death row". AP News. 24 January 2025. Retrieved 24 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: The village head of Kohod in Tangerang Regency, Arsin bin Sanip, disappears after being involved in an argument with the Minister of Agrarian Affairs and Spatial Planning, Nusron Wahid, about the sea fence on the north coast of Tangerang. He is suspected of being involved in corruption and bribery cases.

links.text: -Nazmudin, Acep; Maullana, Irfan (30 January 2025). "Kades Kohod "Menghilang" Setelah Debat dengan Menteri Nusron, Warganya Bingung". bandung.kompas.com (in Indonesian). Kompas. Retrieved 31 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: The Malaysian Maritime Enforcement Agency opens fire on a boat carrying Indonesian migrant workers off the coast of Tanjung Rhu Beach, Selangor State, killing one passenger and injuring four others.

links.text: -"Protesters pelt Malaysian embassy with eggs over Indonesian migrant worker shooting". AP News. 30 January 2025. Retrieved 30 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: 27 January  Four people are killed by a landslide in Mamuju Regency, West Sulawesi.

links.text: -"Empat tewas akibat bencana longsor di Mamuju". Antara News (in Indonesian). 27 January 2025. Retrieved 27 January 2025.-

Data.event_text: 1 February  The Minister of Energy and Mineral Resources sets a policy on the sale of 3 kg gas cylinders and can no longer be done at the retail level, prompting customers of 3 Kg LPG to go to the bases located in various regions that have been registered.

links.text: -Diahwahyuningtyas, Alicia (3 February 2025). "Adakah Syarat dan Batas Pembelian Elpiji 3 Kg di Pangkalan Resmi? Ini Kata Pertamina". Kompas.com. Retrieved 24 February 2025.-
-Rizki, Mochamad Januar. "Polemik Kebijakan Baru Pembelian LPG 3 Kg, Ini Penjelasan Menteri Bahlil". hukumonline.com (in Indonesian). Retrieved 24 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: 4 February  A truck crashes into a queue of cars at a toll booth in Ciawi, West Java, killing eight people and injuring 11 others.

links.text: -"Kecelakaan di Gerbang Tol Ciawi, Korlantas Kerahkan Tim Traffic Accident Analysis". Tempo (in Indonesian). 5 February 2025. Retrieved 5 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: 5 February  Serge Atlaoui is repatriated to France as part of the bilateral agreement signed on 24 January.

links.text: -"Frenchman Atlaoui returns to Paris after reprieve from death row in Indonesia". France 24. 5 February 2025. Retrieved 5 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: 12 February  A court in Banten sentences six members of a poaching gang to up to 12 years' imprisonment for the killing of 26 Javan rhinoceroses in Ujung Kulon National Park from 2018 to 2023.

links.text: -"Indonesia hands lengthy sentences to Javan rhino poachers". France 24. 14 February 2025. Retrieved 14 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: 16 February  Indonesia wins its first gold medal at the Badminton Asia Mixed Team Championships after Muhammad Shohibul Fikri and Daniel Marthin defeat China's Chen Xujun and Huang Di 21-15, 21-9 in the men's doubles at the 2025 edition held in Qingdao, China.

links.text: -"Indonesia beat China to clinch first Asia mixed team badminton title". France 24. 16 February 2025. Retrieved 16 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: 17 February  Student-led protests against the government start throughout several cities in Indonesia, calling for a "Dark Indonesia" movement.

President Prabowo Subianto inaugurates six officials in the first cabinet reshuffle in the Red-White Cabinet, one of whom is Brian Yuliarto as Minister of Higher Education, Science, and Technology replacing Satryo Soemantri Brodjonegoro.

links.text: -Media, Kompas Cyber (19 February 2025). "Enam Pejabat yang Dilantik Prabowo pada "Reshuffle" Perdana". KOMPAS.com (in Indonesian). Retrieved 19 February 2025.-
-Signature, 20detik. "Reshuffle Perdana Kabinet Prabowo-Gibran". detiknews (in Indonesian). Retrieved 19 February 2025.{{cite web}}:  CS1 maint: numeric names: authors list (link)-

Data.event_text: A fire at the Pasaraya Blok M building at Jakarta spreads from the 7th floor, causing hundreds of workers to escape into the building's yard.

links.text: -"Lantai 7 Gedung Pasaraya Blok M Kebakaran". metrotvnews.com. Retrieved 20 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: Following the 2024 Indonesian local elections, 961 regional heads, consisting of 33 governors, 33 vice governors, 363 regents, 362 vice regents, 85 mayors and 85 vice mayors are inaugurated at the central field of presidential palace, Central Jakarta.

links.text: -"3 Pesan Prabowo di Momen Bersejarah Pelantikan 961 Kepala Daerah". news.detik.com. Retrieved 21 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: Secretary general of Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI-P), Hasto Kristiyanto, is officially arrested by the Corruption Eradication Commission (KPK) in the bribery case against commissioner of General Elections Commission, Wahyu Setiawan.

links.text: -Media, Kompas Cyber (20 February 2025). "BREAKING NEWS: Hasto Kristiyanto Resmi Ditahan KPK". Kompas. Retrieved 20 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: 24 February  The Daya Anagata Nusantara Agency for Investment Management is established, and can manage around Rp. 14.72 quadrillion funds (US$ 900 billion).

links.text: -"Indonesia launches new multi-billion-dollar sovereign wealth fund". France 24. 24 February 2025. Retrieved 24 February 2025.-
-Indraini, Anisa. "Apa itu Danantara? Badan Pengelola Investasi yang Baru Diluncurkan Prabowo". detikfinance (in Indonesian). Retrieved 24 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: 25 February  The Attorney General's Office names seven people as suspects in a corruption case involving state-owned energy company PT. Pertamina Patra Niaga, a subsidiary of PT. Pertamina (Persero), and private contractors. The alleged irregularities that occurred between 2018 and 2023 reportedly resulted in state losses of Rp. 193.7 trillion (US$ 12 billion) per year. However, the losses have almost reached Rp1 quadrillion, which is Rp. 968.5 trillion (US$ 58.96 billion).

links.text: -"Pertamina: Kronologi dua pejabat Pertamina jadi tersangka baru kasus korupsi minyak mentah, diduga memerintahkan 'oplos' atau blending RON 90 jadi Pertamax". BBC News Indonesia (in Indonesian). 25 February 2025. Retrieved 13 March 2025.-

-arya.dwiangga@kompas.com, Norbertus Arya Dwiangga Martiar- (4 March 2025). "Betulkah Kerugian Negara dalam Kasus Pertamina Capai Rp 1 Kuadriliun?". Kompas.id (in Indonesian). Retrieved 13 March 2025.-
-"Pertamina Vows Cooperation as Executives Named in $11.9B Corruption Scandal". Jakarta Globe. Archived from the original on 6 March 2025. Retrieved 13 March 2025.-
-"Pertamina Vows Cooperation as Executives Named in $11.9B Corruption Scandal". Jakarta Globe. Archived from the original on 6 March 2025. Retrieved 13 March 2025.-

Data.event_text: 26 February  Industry Minister Agus Gumiwang Kartasasmita announces an agreement with Apple Inc. for the latter to build facilities in Bandung and Batam amid efforts to end a ban by Indonesia on the sale of iPhone 16 devices.

links.text: -Nugraheny, Dian Erika (27 February 2025). "Pemerintah RI-Apple Akhirnya Capai Kesepakatan, iPhone 16 Series Bisa Segera Diperjualbelikan di Indonesia". Kompas.com. Retrieved 13 March 2025.-
-"Indonesia agrees deal with Apple that could end iPhone sales ban". France 24. 26 February 2025. Retrieved 26 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: 28 February  A fire in Pondok Bambu destroys multiple residences.

links.text: -"Kebakaran melanda rumah di permukiman padat Pondok Bambu Jaktim". Antara (in Indonesian). 28 February 2025.-
-"Kebakaran Hebat di Pondok Bambu, Api Melahap Rumah Warga". CNBC Indonesia (in Indonesian). 28 February 2025. Retrieved 28 February 2025.-

Data.event_text: 6 March  Governor of West Java, Dedi Mulyadi orders the demolition of Hibisc Fantasy, an amusement park at Puncak, Bogor Regency that was only opened December last year, due to concerns of causing flash floods in Jakarta.

links.text: -"Mengenal Hibisc Fantasy Puncak, Tempat Wisata yang Dibongkar Dedi Mulyadi". travel.kompas.com. Retrieved 9 March 2025.-

Data.event_text: 10 March  At least 53 inmates escape from the Kutacane Penitentiary in Aceh.

links.text: -"Moment inmates stage prison break in Indonesia". BBC. 12 March 2025. Retrieved 12 March 2025.-

Data.event_text: 17 March  Three policemen are shot dead by two TNI members while raiding a cockfighting arena at the village of Karang Manik in Way Kanan Regency, Lampung.

links.text: -"Kronologi Tiga Polisi Lampung Tewas Ditembak saat Gerebek Sabung Ayam", cnnindonesia.com, retrieved 18 March 2025-

Data.event_text: 18 March  A magnitude 5.6 earthquake hits North Tapanuli Regency in North Sumatra, killing one person.

links.text: -"Gempa di Taput Tewaskan 1 Warga, Rumah Korban Terkena Longsor Saat Tidur" [Earthquake hits Taput Kills 1 Resident, Victim's was Killed by Landslide While Sleeping] (in Indonesian). Detik.com. 18 March 2025. Retrieved 18 March 2025.-

Data.event_text: The House of Representatives (DPR) officially ratifies the revision of Indonesian National Armed Forces Law, which would allow military officers to hold civilian office without leaving the service, in a plenary session.

links.text: -"Rapat Paripurna DPR Setujui RUU TNI Disahkan Menjadi Undang-Undang". antaranews.com. 20 March 2025. Retrieved 20 March 2025.-
-"Anger as Indonesia law allows military bigger role in government". BBC. 20 March 2025. Retrieved 20 March 2025.-

Data.event_text: The Lewotobi volcano erupts in Flores, cancelling flights.

links.text: -"Indonesia's Mount Lewotobi Laki Laki volcano erupts, prompting alert level to be raised". AP News. 21 March 2025.-

Data.event_text: 26 March — One person is killed while two others are reported missing following the collapse of a nickel waste disposal site in the Morowali Industrial Park.

links.text: -"Sludge collapse kills 1 at a Chinese-funded nickel plant in Indonesia". AP News. 26 March 2025.-

Data.event_text: 3 April — Ten people are killed in a landslide that buries two vehicles along a hilly road near Watu Lumpang in Mojokerto Regency, East Java.

links.text: -"10 dead as landslide hits passing cars on Indonesia's Java island". AP News. 4 April 2025.-

Data.event_text: 9 April — Seventeen people are killed in an attack by the West Papua National Liberation Army on a gold panning camp in Yahukimo Regency, Highland Papua.

links.text: -"Indonesia says 17 people slain by Papua rebels were gold miners". AP News. 11 April 2025.-

Data.event_text: 17 April — Minister of Public Works Dody Hanggodo dissolves the Capital City of Nusantara Infrastructure Construction Task Force.

links.text: -"Satgas Pembangunan IKN Resmi Dibubarkan". liputan6.com. Retrieved 19 April 2025.-
